<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1155,1192,1460]" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duarte and Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[160,390,1227,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ebeninus">
<emphasis box="[160,390,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">Gibboryctes ebeninus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[601,815,1227,1252]" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis box="[601,728,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">Gibboryctes</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: Body colouration black (
<figureCitation box="[583,673,1262,1287]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1050,1073]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,191,1006]" captionTargetId="figure-170@5.[162,1154,142,1018]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov. (a, b) Habitus of paratype female in dorsal and lateral views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758319/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">Figure 2</figureCitation>
); labrum subtrapezoidal, bearing truncated apical margin (
<figureCitation box="[326,418,1297,1322]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="9.[160,225,1090,1113]" captionTargetBox="[166,1145,146,1050]" captionTargetId="figure-188@9.[166,1149,142,1058]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 6. Labrum in dorsal view. (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758331/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(b)); maxillary palpomere II long, about 2.8 times longer than wide at middle (
<figureCitation box="[281,374,1331,1356]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1161,1184]" captionTargetBox="[167,1127,143,1126]" captionTargetId="figure-61@11.[166,1149,142,1129]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Right maxilla in ventral view. (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Red arrows indicating triangular galea in (a), elongate maxillary palpomere II in (b), lobed inner margin of galea and stipe with triangular lobe in (c), pointed and triangular teeth on galea in (d), scythe-shape d teeth and rounded inner margin of galea in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758335/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(b)); head with punctate frons (
<figureCitation box="[720,824,1331,1356]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="14.[160,225,1441,1464]" captionTargetBox="[168,1146,144,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-42@14.[166,1149,142,1410]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 11. Detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs of females in dorsal view: (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi;(b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedi sp.nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Arrow indicates punctate frons in (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758341/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(b)); pronotal anterior corners weakly punctate (punctures predominantly spaced above 1 diameter of punctures) (
<figureCitation box="[168,274,1401,1426]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[160,225,1189,1212]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,146,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-100@15.[166,1149,142,1157]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. Females of Gibboryctes species with detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs in lateral view and left elytra in dorsal view, respectively. (a,b) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (c,d) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (e,f) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov. Jsi, juxtasutural interstria. Arrow indicates coalescent punctures in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758343/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">Figure 12</figureCitation>
(c)); juxtasutural interstriae with scarce and large punctures, confined on anterior area of elytra (
<figureCitation box="[369,476,1435,1460]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[160,225,1189,1212]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,146,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-100@15.[166,1149,142,1157]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. Females of Gibboryctes species with detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs in lateral view and left elytra in dorsal view, respectively. (a,b) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (c,d) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (e,f) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov. Jsi, juxtasutural interstria. Arrow indicates coalescent punctures in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758343/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="210">Figure 12</figureCitation>
(d)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
